1781066666067002	sigil-dev	itc:v3:AWLOeSZkkyTnmRAAAAAAQd3q2q1d7QAAAAExBA		item.create	bn-36zz	{"description":"During a multi-workspace session in sigil (8 workspaces, frequent epoch advances), every conflicted replay produced ONE structured conflict block per file containing the ENTIRE file three times (epoch/base/workspace) — e.g. globals.rs ballooned to 11,586 lines for what git merge-file resolves as ~10 small hunks. Agents had to redo proper three-way merges manually (git merge-file with base/theirs/mine commits) to get workable hunks. Also: marker labels say only 'epoch (current)' / 'workspace changes' — embedding the actual commit SHAs (base/theirs/mine) in the markers or the conflict commit message would let resolvers reconstruct the merge mechanically. Round 1 markers had no base section at all; later rounds were diff3-style, which helped but were still whole-file.","kind":"task","title":"Auto-rebase/sync writes whole-file diff3 conflicts instead of minimal hunks"}	blake3:9u_NozgY0HIgNM60_geBt0KWStFmysJaLmi4tXm4S-k
1781066677129914	sigil-dev	itc:v3:AWLOeSZkkyTnmRAAAAAAQd3q2q1d7QAAAAExBQ		item.create	bn-21cj	{"description":"Observed in sigil repo: 'maw ws sync <ws>' printed 'Rebase complete: 1 commit(s) replayed cleanly' but had actually written a whole-file structured diff3 conflict (with '# structured conflict at src/run_cli.rs' header) into the file and committed it to the workspace HEAD. The agent only discovered it because a later build failed. 'Replayed cleanly' must never be printed when conflict content was committed; the summary line should match what maw ws resolve --list reports.","kind":"task","title":"maw ws sync reports 'replayed cleanly' while committing a structured conflict into HEAD"}	blake3:6x1SSGZFxHnVMcy0qSpBHygB4-8a3cpwmmVfg5PG_Ow
1781066692054427	sigil-dev	itc:v3:AWLOeSZkkyTnmRAAAAAAQd3q2q1d7QAAAAExBg		item.create	bn-8zqz	{"description":"After an agent manually resolved committed conflict markers and committed: 'maw ws conflicts <ws>' said 'No conflicts found / 1 workspace(s) can be merged cleanly', but 'maw ws merge <ws> --into default --check' BLOCKED with '1 unresolved conflict(s)' and 'maw ws resolve --list' agreed with the blocker ('1 structured conflict, sides=[epoch, ws]') — while the file itself contained zero markers. An extra 'maw ws sync' printed 'Cleared stale conflict metadata after a manual resolution commit' and unblocked the merge. Seen twice in one session (two different workspaces). The three commands should read the same source of truth, and a manual resolution commit should clear the metadata without requiring a follow-up sync.","kind":"task","title":"Conflict state inconsistent across ws conflicts / merge --check / resolve --list; stale metadata needs manual sync"}	blake3:qigPn3Gx9FvJHDEiRyrryVmllolYnBMwA6ZGL9y3y8Y
1781066700187734	sigil-dev	itc:v3:AWLOeSZkkyTnmRAAAAAAQd3q2q1d7QAAAAExBw		item.create	bn-1abp	{"description":"UX cluster from a multi-agent sigil session: (1) 'maw ws merge' auto-rebase rewrites sibling worktrees ('worktree synced') with no notification to agents working in them — one agent saw a file go from 1377 to 1506 lines between reads ('file modified since read' edit rejections) and reported the workspace 'changed underneath me'; consider an opt-out, a marker file, or at least documenting that active workspaces mutate. (2) Once a workspace is behind the epoch, EVERY 'maw exec' prints the 'Workspace is behind the current epoch... Skipping auto-sync' warning — duplicated 2-3x per invocation, including during the exact 'git add && git commit' remediation sequence the warning itself recommends. (3) Minor related: 'maw ws sync --rebase' warns the flag is deprecated-default while edict-managed AGENTS.md still documents the flagged form; 'maw ws diff <ws>' prints nothing for a committed-but-unmerged workspace though AGENTS.md describes it as 'diff vs epoch'; 'maw exec' errors with 'Not in a Manifold repository' when run from outside the repo even though the workspace arg identifies the target; 'maw ws create --from main' actually bases on the current epoch, not branch-tip main, when they diverge.","kind":"task","title":"Auto-rebase rewrites active sibling worktrees silently; stale-epoch warning is noisy and mistimed"}	blake3:bsdZLbOzvTMNeHdh5rBYY2bns2lqyqrjNoenPBabe6E
1781089900558738	bob	itc:v3:AWKSc8kyZJPJk5EAAAAAQau9WtV610AAAAEznwI		item.update	bn-1abp	{"field":"title","value":"Auto-rebase rewrites active sibling worktrees silently; stale-epoch warning is noisy and mistimed"}	blake3:hJLcv-k2LP_EriiKDWwFoWuC-0Yc_GEWya5dCCYcp0M
1781089900608573	bob	itc:v3:AWKSc8kyZJPJk5EAAAAAQau9WtV610AAAAEzoAI		item.update	bn-1abp	{"field":"description","value":"UX cluster from a multi-agent sigil session: (1) 'maw ws merge' auto-rebase rewrites sibling worktrees ('worktree synced') with no notification to agents working in them — one agent saw a file go from 1377 to 1506 lines between reads ('file modified since read' edit rejections) and reported the workspace 'changed underneath me'; consider an opt-out, a marker file, or at least documenting that active workspaces mutate. (2) Once a workspace is behind the epoch, EVERY 'maw exec' prints the 'Workspace is behind the current epoch... Skipping auto-sync' warning — duplicated 2-3x per invocation, including during the exact 'git add && git commit' remediation sequence the warning itself recommends. (3) Minor related: 'maw ws sync --rebase' warns the flag is deprecated-default while edict-managed AGENTS.md still documents the flagged form; 'maw ws diff <ws>' prints nothing for a committed-but-unmerged workspace though AGENTS.md describes it as 'diff vs epoch'; 'maw exec' errors with 'Not in a Manifold repository' when run from outside the repo even though the workspace arg identifies the target; 'maw ws create --from main' actually bases on the current epoch, not branch-tip main, when they diverge."}	blake3:9ila3G2GJzXSYvGdVFwUgKdH3qIE4kCgfd17t35orZw
