1781089956585665	bob	itc:v3:AWKSc8kyZJPJk5EAAAAAQau9WtV610AAAAEzrwI		item.update	bn-36zz	{"field":"description","value":"During a multi-workspace session in sigil (8 workspaces, frequent epoch advances), every conflicted replay produced ONE structured conflict block per file containing the ENTIRE file three times (epoch/base/workspace) — e.g. globals.rs ballooned to 11,586 lines for what git merge-file resolves as ~10 small hunks. Agents had to redo proper three-way merges manually (git merge-file with base/theirs/mine commits) to get workable hunks. Also: marker labels say only 'epoch (current)' / 'workspace changes' — embedding the actual commit SHAs (base/theirs/mine) in the markers or the conflict commit message would let resolvers reconstruct the merge mechanically. Round 1 markers had no base section at all; later rounds were diff3-style, which helped but were still whole-file."}	blake3:bamDoa8KyT-UIzvGO4U9cYCFqslr40DKt69lVuxq4iI
1781089956621256	bob	itc:v3:AWKSc8kyZJPJk5EAAAAAQau9WtV610AAAAEzsAI		item.update	bn-36zz	{"field":"kind","value":"bug"}	blake3:mVbBboWNpxqVhISxOTgSXnEpQIb66OZlK2nZpUrRWLU
